# ENIP Scanner Configuration

menu "EtherNet/IP Scanner Configuration"

    config ENIP_SCANNER_ENABLE_DEBUG_LOGS
        bool "Enable debug logging"
        default n
        help
            Enable verbose debug logging for EtherNet/IP scanner operations.
            This can be useful for troubleshooting but will increase log output.

    config ENIP_SCANNER_MAX_DEVICES
        int "Maximum number of devices to scan"
        range 1 256
        default 32
        help
            Maximum number of devices that can be discovered in a single scan operation.

    config ENIP_SCANNER_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS
        int "Default timeout (milliseconds)"
        range 1000 60000
        default 5000
        help
            Default timeout for EtherNet/IP operations in milliseconds.

    config ENIP_SCANNER_ENABLE_TAG_SUPPORT
        bool "Enable Allen-Bradley tag support"
        default n
        help
            Enable support for reading/writing Allen-Bradley tags (Micro800, CompactLogix, etc.).
            This adds tag-specific functions but increases code size.
            Note: Tag names must be known in advance (no tag discovery/browsing).

    config ENIP_SCANNER_ENABLE_MOTOMAN_SUPPORT
        bool "Enable Motoman robot CIP class support"
        default n
        help
            Enable support for reading/writing Motoman vendor-specific CIP classes (0x70-0x81).
            This adds functions for robot status, I/O, variables, and registers.
            Reference: Motoman Manual 165838-1CD, Section 5.2

    config ENIP_SCANNER_ENABLE_IMPLICIT_SUPPORT
        bool "Enable implicit messaging (I/O data) support"
        default y
        help
            Enable support for EtherNet/IP implicit messaging (Class 1 I/O data).
            This adds functions for establishing bidirectional implicit connections using
            Forward Open/Close and UDP-based cyclic I/O data exchange.
            Uses UDP port 2222 for implicit I/O and TCP port 44818 for Forward Open/Close.
            Reference: EtherNet/IP Implicit Messaging Implementation Guide

endmenu

